| **Universal Human Rights Expansion** – Food, housing, clean water, health care, and digital privacy will be codified as *basic rights* in most national constitutions. | Industries that deny or commodify these rights (e.g., predatory drug pricing, exploitative labor) will be deemed violations of human dignity. |
| **Digital Transparency & Open Knowledge** – Data about supply chains, emissions, labor conditions, and animal welfare will be openly accessible in real time. | Hidden harms will become impossible to conceal; public scrutiny will force rapid reform or reputational collapse. |
| **Circular‑Economy Imperative** – Resource scarcity will drive policy that *must* keep materials in use. | Linear “take‑make‑dispose” models will be viewed as primitive and criminally wasteful. |

