| Replacement | Core Technologies | Societal Mechanisms |
|---|---|---|
| **Cultivated Food & Alternative Proteins** | Cellular agriculture, precision fermentation, AI‑optimized nutrient media | **Just‑Transition Funds** financed by the Common Food Fund; certification schemes guaranteeing animal‑free status. |
| **Renewable Energy & Grid‑Scale Storage** | Fusion pilots, space‑based solar power, solid‑state batteries | **Carbon‑Pricing + Global Energy Equity Framework**; mandatory renewable‑share contracts for all producers. |
| **Circular Textiles & Materials** | 3‑D knitting, mycelium leather, biodegradable composites | Extended Producer Responsibility (EPR) laws; “material‑as‑service” contracts that keep ownership with manufacturers. |
| **Regenerative Agriculture** | Cover‑crop AI, microbial inoculants, satellite‑guided precision farming | **Payment for Ecosystem Services** (carbon credits, biodiversity offsets) that reward farms meeting R‑Principles. |
